PROPOSAL: pulse-initial-2026-03-03
STATUS: pending
TIER: T1
FILE: core/pulse.py
AUTHOR: Shiva (Claude Code) + Sean Campbell

SUMMARY
-------
Initial implementation of PULSE — the daemon worker and heartbeat.

PULSE is what makes the system breathe. It loops at 30-second intervals,
picks tasks from GRAFT, runs them through registered handlers, manages a
recurring schedule, and tracks its own health. Without PULSE, tasks sit
in GRAFT forever. With PULSE, the system self-drives.

DESIGN DECISIONS
----------------
1. tick() is the testable unit. The daemon loop just calls tick() every 30s.
   Testing doesn't require spinning a thread.
2. handlers dict: {handler_name: callable(username, metadata) → dict}.
   Built-ins (soil_drain, loam_backfill_summaries, loam_backfill_embeddings)
   are pre-registered if their modules are importable.
3. 3-failure backoff: per-handler failure counter. After 3 consecutive
   failures, backoff doubles (30s → 60s → 120s → max 300s). Resets on success.
4. archive_stale() runs on daemon startup. Moves completed/failed tasks
   older than N days to graft_archive table. Keeps graft.db lean.
5. Recurring schedules stored in pulse.db (schedules table).
   due_schedules() returns jobs where next_run <= now.
6. Daemon runs in a background thread. stop() sets a threading.Event.
7. health() returns last_tick, tasks_processed (session total), errors,
   uptime_seconds, schedule_count.
8. Caller provides all db_paths. No path logic inside.

PUBLIC API
----------
init_tables(db_path) → None

# Scheduler
add_schedule(db_path, username, name, handler_name,
             interval_seconds, metadata=None) → str
list_schedules(db_path, username) → list[dict]
remove_schedule(db_path, schedule_id) → bool
due_schedules(db_path, username) → list[dict]

# Tick (testable unit)
tick(graft_db_path, pulse_db_path, username, handlers,
     max_tasks=5) → dict  # {tasks_processed, schedules_ran, errors}

# Daemon
start(graft_db_path, pulse_db_path, username, handlers,
      poll_interval=30) → threading.Thread
stop() → None

# Maintenance
archive_stale(graft_db_path, username, older_than_days=7) → int
health(pulse_db_path, username) → dict

SCHEMA (pulse.db)
-----------------
schedules  — (schedule_id TEXT PK, username, name, handler_name,
              interval_seconds INT, last_run TEXT, next_run TEXT,
              enabled INT DEFAULT 1, consecutive_failures INT DEFAULT 0,
              metadata TEXT)
pulse_log  — (id, username, tick_at TEXT, tasks_processed INT,
              schedules_ran INT, errors INT)

